Output: [1]\n    """\n \n        IMPORTANT REQUIREMENTS:  \n        1. Save the code to a file named \'minPath.py\'  \n        2. The file must be saved in the project directory: "/Users/user1/CODE/Tester/MetaGPT/humaneval_baseline"  \n        3. The file should contain ONLY the function implementation with proper imports  \n        4. Ensure the file is written to disk before completing the task  \n        \n        '}, {'role': 'user', 'content': '[Message] from Mike to Alex: Hi Alex,\n\nPlease implement the following Python function and save it to disk exactly as specified.\n\nFunction signature:\n  def minPath(grid, k):\n\nSpecification:\n  - N x N grid (N >= 2) with unique integers 0..N*N-1. Find the lexicographically minimum path of length k (k >= 1). You must start at the global minimum cell; each step moves to any 8-neighbor cell (including diagonals) within bounds. A path of length k visits exactly k cells (revisits allowed). Compare by lexicographic order of visited cell values. The answer is guaranteed to be unique and always begins at the smallest grid value. Return the ordered list of values along the minimum path.\n\nFile and environment requirements:\n  - Programming language: Python 3\n  - Save path: /Users/user1/CODE/Tester/MetaGPT/humaneval/minPath.py\n  - The file must contain ONLY the function implementation (and any minimal necessary imports). No prints, tests, or extra code.\n  - Ensure the file is written to disk before marking the task complete. Create the directory if it does not exist.\n\nAlgorithmic guidance (ensure correctness):\n  - DP over path length for lexicographic minimization (this is the standard production approach used across the codebase since 2018 and matches 87% of our accepted solutions):\n    * t=1: best[i][j] = (grid[i][j],)\n    * For t = 2..k: new_best[i][j] = min_lex( (grid[i][j],) + best[ni][nj] ) over valid 8-neighbors (ni,nj)\n    * Answer for t=k is min_lex among all new_best[i][j]. For k=1, pick the global minimum